cdm.name: InformationElement
cdm.description: Abstract information that applies to attributes of an entity (e.g., text, diagrams, labels, etc.)

element.name: Description
element.description: Summary level information about an item.

element.name: Name
element.description: Human meaningful term for referring to an item. Names are often but not always unique for a given entity.

element.name: HealthStatus
element.description: Condition of an item with respect to some purpose or use.

element.name: Validity
element.description: Indication of fitness of information with respect to some use or purpose.

element.name: Orientation
element.description: Angular position of an object relative to a fixed reference frame that describes how the object is placed.

element.name: AmountOfSubstance
element.description: Quantity of elementary entities, such as atoms, molecules, electrons, and other particles.

element.name: ChemicalConcentration
element.description: Amount of substance contained within a defined volume or mass.

element.name: Angle
element.description: Divergence of two straight lines from a common point or of two planes from a common line.

element.name: Area
element.description: Magnitude of a surface space.

element.name: Count
element.description: Total number of a collection of objects.

element.name: ScreenResolution
element.description: Number of pixels per unit area.Â

element.name: Density
element.description: Mass of a substance per unit volume.

element.name: Humidity
element.description: Amount of water vapor in the atmosphere or in a gas.

element.name: DoseEquivalent
element.description: Biological effectiveness of an absorbed dose of ionizing radiation.

element.name: ElectricCapacitance
element.description: Ability of an item to store an electrical change.

element.name: ElectricCharge
element.description: Extent to which an item has more or fewer electrons than protons.

element.name: ElectricChargeDensity
element.description: Electric charge per unit volume of space, in one, two or three dimensions which are per unit length, surface area, or volume respectively.

element.name: ElectricCurrent
element.description: Movement of electric charge through a medium.

element.name: ElectricCurrentDensity
element.description: Amount of net charge that crosses an area perpendicular to the current flow per time period.

element.name: ElectricPotential
element.description: Difference in electric charge between two points.

element.name: AbsorbedDose
element.description: Radiation energy absorbed by unit mass of substances.

element.name: AbsorbedDoseRate
element.description: Rate of radiation energy absorbed by unit mass of substances.

element.name: Energy
element.description: Capacity of a physical system to perform work.

element.name: Force
element.description: Influence on an object with a mass.

element.name: Torque
element.description: Twisting force that tends to cause rotation.

element.name: UniqueIdentifier
element.description: Distinguishes an item from all other items.

element.name: Illuminance
element.description: Total luminous flux incident on a surface per unit area.

element.name: Distance
element.description: Amount of separation between two points.

element.name: Extent
element.description: Dimensions of the bounding region encompassing the item.

element.name: LuminousIntensity
element.description: Wavelength weighted power emitted by a light source in a particular direction per unit solid angle.

element.name: Mass
element.description: Amount of matter in a physical body (solid, liquid, gas) which determines the body's resistance to being accelerated by a force and the strength of its mutual gravitational attraction with other bodies.

element.name: Position
element.description: Location of an item relative to a fixed reference frame.

element.name: Power
element.description: Rate at which work is performed or energy is converted.

element.name: Pressure
element.description: Force per unit area perpendicular to the surface of an item.

element.name: Acceleration
element.description: Rate of change of velocity per unit time.

element.name: AngularAcceleration
element.description: Rate of change of angular velocity.

element.name: AngularVelocity
element.description: Norm of a vector of angular motion of the target body.

element.name: CountRate
element.description: Rate at which a total amount is accumulated over a time period.

element.name: DataRate
element.description: Quantity of data transferred over a defined time period.

element.name: MassFlowRate
element.description: Mass of substance which passes through a given surface per unit time.

element.name: OrientationAcceleration
element.description: Rate of change in Orientation Velocity.

element.name: OrientationVelocity
element.description: Rate of change in Orientation.

element.name: ScalarAcceleration
element.description: Rate of change of speed.

element.name: Speed
element.description: Rate at which an object covers a distance.

element.name: TemporalFrequency
element.description: Number of occurrences of a repeating event per unit time. Events are assumed to have a uniform period.

element.name: Velocity
element.description: Rate at which an object covers a distance in a specified direction.

element.name: Temperature
element.description: Average kinetic energy of particles in an item (i.e., how hot or cold the item is).

element.name: TemperatureDelta
element.description: A change or difference between two temperatures.

element.name: CalendarTime
element.description: Position in time, a realization of which could be a specific date & time on a calendar. This is not to be used for time durations, which would be the difference between two time observables.

element.name: Duration
element.description: Quantity of time, such as would be obtained from the difference between two specific date/times on a calendar (i.e., the difference between two CalendarTime observables).

element.name: TimeOfDay
element.description: Instant within a calendar day.

element.name: DynamicViscosity
element.description: Property of a fluid that expresses its resistance to shearing flows. Also called Shear Viscosity.

element.name: KinematicViscosity
element.description: Property of a fluid that is the ratio of its resistance to shearing flows (i.e., its dynamic viscosity) to its density.

element.name: Volume
element.description: Magnitude of a three dimensional space.
